quizzes.textContent:
[h1]The background-image Property[/h1]

The [b]background-image[/b] property sets one or several background images in an element. Let's set a background-image for the <body> element.

[b]The CSS:[/b][code format="css" codeId="546"]body {
  [b] background-image: url("css_logo.png");[/b]
   background-color: #e9e9e9;
}[/code]
[note]The [b]url [/b]specifies the path to the image file. Both relative and absolute paths are supported.[/note]
[b]Result: [/b][img id="2626" width="100%"]
[note]By default, a background-image is placed at the top-left corner of an element, and is repeated both vertically and horizontally to cover the entire element.[/note]

